hopper Sandwich from Burger King: Burger King advertises the Whopper as “America’s Favorite Burger”, and there’s no doubting its iconic status. More than 11 million customers walk through Burger King’s doors each day, many of them in pursuit of the famous burger.\n\n2. Cheeseburger from Five Guys: Five Guys still holds the title of #1 fan-favorite burger chain, replacing two-time winner In-n-Out, 2018. Their cheeseburger is a classic staple on the menu.\n\n3. Original Recipe Chicken from KFC: KFC’s Original Recipe Chicken is famous for its secret 11 herbs and spices, and also for launching the brand into fast food superstardom.\n\n4. Chicken Sandwich from Chick-fil-A: Chick-fil-A may be politically polarizing, but people tend to have a unified stance on their original Chicken Sandwich: “delicious.”\n\n5. Pepperoni Pizza from Domino’s: Domino’s may be the number two pizza chain in America, but it’s quickly gaining steam on Pizza Hut and could surpass it in popularity by next year. According to QSR Magazine, its Pepperoni Pizza is easily the most delivered item on the menu.\n\n6. Whataburger Taquito with Cheese: According to Bon Appetit, Texans are down to ride or die for Whataburger. The Taquito with Cheese has, in particular, been called “a Texas tradition” but its popularity extends beyond the lone star state.\n\n7. Burger King French Fries: It’s possible that all French fries, being a natural sidekick to burgers, are some of the most highly ordered items at any fast food chain. That said; according to Business Insider Burger King Fries deserve their popularity based on merit.\n\nBest Home Made 5 Fast Food Recipes:\nTo consider your health with save yourself from some fat, you can re-create your favorite fast foods at home. Think about burgers, fries, cheese sticks and more. In the face of recent additions and alterations to menus, fast food remains a flat belly nightmare.\n\nWe know the food is shortening our lives and expanding our waistlines, and yet, every day 9.6 million Americans visits one of these chains. That’s why we have rounded up very common 5 recipes that flawlessly copy the responsible parties, but won’t leave you with high cholesterol and rolls of belly fat. You are welcome anytime.\n\nCHICKEN NUGGETS:\nNutrition: 258 calories, 14.1 g fat (2.2 g saturated), 65 mg sodium, 8.7 g carbs, 2.4 g fiber, &lt;1 g sugar, 24.5 g protein (calculated without salt).\n\nThese golden nuggets are crusted with almonds, one of the best nuts for a lower BMI. In fact, a 2003 study demonstrated that munching on these nuts gave dieters left dieters more satisfied and less likely to overeat, thus increasing weight loss.\n\nResource: Get the recipe from Gimme Some Oven.\n\nFRENCH FRIES:\nNutrition: 202 calories, 7.2 g fat (1 g saturated), 11 mg sodium, 32.3 g carbs, 4.1 g fiber, 1.4 g sugar, 3.7 g protein.\n\nOne serving of these potato wedges contains 61% of your daily vitamin C quota, a vitamin that keeps more than the occasional sniffles away. In fact, C has also been shown to elevate mood and counteract the stress hormones that leave you feeling tense and trigger the storage of belly fat.\n\nResource: Get the recipe from To Her Core.\n\nMOZZARELLA STICKS:\nNutrition: 98 calories, 5.5 g fat (3.1 g saturated), 213 mg sodium, 5.4 g carbs, 0 g fiber, 0 g sugar, 7.1 g protein.\n\nMozzarella sticks and body goals make one contradictory couple. But with just 98 calories and 5.4 carbs, these mouthwatering golden breaded cheese sticks fit flawlessly into any diet.\n\nResource: Get the recipe from Creme de la Crumb.\n\nCHOCOLATE SHAKE:\nNutrition: 151 calories, 8.5 g fat (2 g saturated), 17.5 g carbs, 4 g fiber, 10.5 g sugar, 3.5 g protein.\n\nBlend this waist-whittling shake instead. Just make sure to opt for unripe bananas, which are rich in resistant starch. When we ingest foods that resist digestion, the gut produces healthy bacteria, leading to lowered appetite and more efficient fat oxidation. In fact, one study found that replacing just 5 percent of the day’s carbohydrates with a source of resistant starch can boost post-meal fat burn by up to 30 percent!\n\nResource: Get the recipe from Minimalist Baker.\n\nPEPPERONI PIZZA:\nNutrition: 298 calories, 5.3 g fat (2 g saturated), 293 mg sodium, 47.8 g carbs, 2.4 g fiber, 6.7 g sugar, 13.6 g protein ***calculated with 1/2 cup part-skim mozzarella, plus 1 cup organic tomato sauce, ¼ cup pepperoni, and no salt.\n\nMaybe the Pizza Hut will show you how flawlessly Greek yogurt blends into pizza dough, packing in protein, calcium, and vitamin D—but this recipe will. Thank the Greek Gods for this one.\n\nResource: Get the recipe from The Baker Mama.\n\nRecommendation:\n\nHow do you make healthy fast food?\n1. Make sure your fast food salad isn\'t a stealth diet saboteur.\n2. Choose low-fat and fat-free dressing and ask for it on the side, so you can control how much you use.\n3. Skip high-fat toppings such as bacon bits, cheese, croutons, and crispy noodles. ...\n4. Avoid taco salads. ...\n5. Choose salads with grilled chicken, shrimp, or vegetables.\n\nWhat makes fast food taste good?\nThe alluring smell of fast-food increases people\'s sense of taste when they eat it, causing the experience to be more enjoyable. Fast food contains additives that are high in sugar and fat. These are one of the main reasons that fast food is so delicious.', 'Best fast food and recipes in the Christmas', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '147-autosave-v1', '', '', '2019-08-16 05:48:36', '2019-08-16 05:48:36', '', 147, 'http://sajedaiub.com/Development/affiliate_app/147-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0);
