(221, 2, '2019-08-17 11:39:04', '2019-08-17 11:39:04', 'Famous artworks forever:\nPainting is an image or artwork created using pigments or color on an outer surface such as paper or canvas. The pigment or coloring may be in a wet, pastels, or dry form. Many of these paintings are evidence of the skill and talents of many artists from different parts of the world. Pablo Picasso said that every child is a born artist; the problem is to retain that artist within themselves.\n\nPeople love painting because painting is a form of expression, if done right, it can show a plethora of emotions. Each color has significance and sometimes, people want to express through paintings, rather than words. Science says that painting can help us reduce stress and may develop happy hormones in the body.\n\nThe best paintings simply take your breath away! \nThis creation is full of art and inspiration, that is what everyone can see, but it takes a really talented and visionary artist to pick paint and brush and illustrate their thoughts, visions and this beautiful creation into paintings.\n\n\nImportance of painting:\nPainting is much more than a simple activity. It is a way, where different types of children can express themselves in their own special way. Painting also helps children to use their senses, emotion, explore color, and create pleasing works and experiences.\n\n\nMost Beautiful and Expensive Paintings forever:\nThe viewers have seen the huge number of paintings in museums and art galleries across the world, only a relatively number of artworks have been universally recognized as being classic and famous. Everlasting in their beauty and implementation, these artworks have limits of time and artistic concepts to create history. These famous paintings are familiar to people of all ages and cultures. The greatest works of art ever created and will continue to vibrate in the minds of art lovers for many centuries to come. \n\nOur expert of art group identified 7 most famous paintings in the world that have had the maximum artistic impact and recognition. This art list comprises works by a great many famed artists that are now housed in some of the world’s finest museums. Yet, the list of top 7 masterpieces is only an acknowledgment of the huge contribution of the artists who have made them so memorable.\n\n\nHistory of top 7 Masterpieces - World\'s Most Famous Paintings:\nTo blow, we have gone through great detail to find some of the best artwork that has ever been produced. Below are 7 most beautiful, famous and expensive paintings of all time.\n\n\nOur Top #1 \nMonalisa: Probably the most famous painting in the world is Monalisa by Leonardo da Vinci. This is a portrait of a lady called Gherardini and world-famous because the lady’s expression is indecipherable. This painting is currently displayed in Louvre, France.\n\n\nOur Top #2\nSchool of Athens: The famous painting is painted by Raphael; this painting contains photos of world-famous philosophers like Plato and Aristotle walking within the middle in conjunction with other philosophers on the sides. It is now located in the Vatican.\n\nOur Top #3 \nThe Girl with a Pearl Earring: The Girl with a Pearl Earring is usually called Dutch Monalisa because of the facial expression of the girl. It is hard to recognize. This painting by Johannes Vermeer has her pearl earrings because of the attentiveness.\n\nOur Top #4\nNight Watch: This painting is one of the most popular pieces of work by Rembrandt. It depicts a whole town moving out led by its captain. A unique aspect is its dark varnish that gives an impression of the night scene. It is currently housed in Rijksmuseum in Amsterdam.\n\nOur Top #5 \nChristina’s World: Christina’s World is one of the most famous paintings of the 20th century. The painting of 1948’s canvas represents a lady, Anna Christina who is crawling up from a yellowish-brown grass field and looking lovingly at a gray farmhouse on the top of the crag. The lady within the painting was stricken by a muscular disorder that prevented her from hiking.  However, she was still doing an endeavor to induce the house that was located quite distant.\n\nNote: Christina’s World is one of the most famous paintings by American painter Andrew Wyeth. The challenge here for the artist was to do impartiality to her extraordinary conquest of a life which most people would consider hopeless. The beautiful painting with a deep meaning and want to realize is currently on show at the Museum of Modern Art in New York.\n\nOur Top #6\nNightHawks: Edward Hopper’s Nighthawks is one painting that represents the elusive assessment of today’s society. The four characters within the painting are isolated and disconnected from their atmosphere despite being in an exceedingly stylish atmosphere.\nOn the outside, it looks that the man and woman are holding hands however on closer inspection but they are not even looking at each other. The other two characters of the painting also look like talking to each other however they are not.\nNote: The painting was bought immediately after it was completed by Hopper by the Art Institute of Chicago which remains there to date. Although Hopper claimed that the situational location was real, however, people were not able to find any such restaurant. The painting gives the idea that everyone in this world is alone since the characters are disconnected and placed in an ambiguous relationship. The painting was created by Hopper in 1942 on canvas and was painted with oil.\n\n\nOur Top #7\nThe Scream: The famous painting of Scream is a painting by Edvard Munch of Norway and it shows the distorted face of a figure against a bloody sky. The hill landscape within the background adds to this picture’s charm. It is also one of the first few paintings done in the expressionism style where the reality is blurred to give more importance to emotions.\n\n\nRecommendation:\nOf course, there are millions of paintings, but we hardly try to well introduce and know about the world-famous painting. Though, here is our list of the most famous 7 paintings ever done. Which of these is your favorite? Do let us know through your comments.\n\nHere are six great benefits of painting that promote mental health and improve your overall quality of life such as,\nFosters Creative Growth. ... \nStrengthens Memory. ... \nBuilds Problem-Solving and Motor Skills. ... \nOffers Stress Relief. ... \nPromotes an Optimistic Attitude. ... \nNurtures Emotional Growth.\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n', 'World famous fine artworks forever', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '218-autosave-v1', '', '', '2019-08-17 11:39:04', '2019-08-17 11:39:04', '', 218, 'http://sajedaiub.com/Development/affiliate_app/218-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0);
